### Instruction:
How do you align a row of divs to the right using flex in css?  Show me an example.

### Response:

To align a row of divs to the right using flex in CSS, you can use the "flex-direction" property set to "row". Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates this:

```css
<style>
  .container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
  }

  .div1, .div2, .div3 {
    width: 100px;
    height: 50px;
    background-color: red;
  }
</style>
```

In this example, we have a container with the "flex" display set and the "row" value for the "flex-direction". Inside the container, we have three divs (.div1, .div2, .div3) that are displayed as flex items. The width, height, and background color of these divs can be customized to fit your needs.

By setting the "flex-direction" property to "row", the div elements will align horizontally from left to right within their container.
